td.div: English: The Syrian Independence flag, the flag of Syria from 1932-58 and 1961-63. Taken up in 2011 by the Syrian opposition.
العربية: علم الثورة السورية، وهو العلم الذي استخدم في سوريا في الفترة (1932-1958).

tr.td: Own work. Based on this source: Flags of the World - Historical Flags Since 1932 (Syria).
See File history below for details.

a.title: Edit section: Interpretation of the colors

tr.td: The Hashemite dynasty, bloody struggle for freedom.
The Umayyad dynasty, bright and peaceful future.
The Fatimid dynasty, the takbīr (the phrase Allahu akbar, meaning "God is great" in Arabic)
